{"kind":"textbox","id":"sh/be5cv6lg","slide":2,"text":"Source: Polymarket resolution documentation · docs.polymarket.com/concepts/resolution","textPreview":"Source: Polymarket resolution documentation · docs.polymarket.com/concepts/resolution","textChars":85,"textLines":1,"bbox":[64,646,960,22]}
{"kind":"textbox","id":"sh/adwvm14v","slide":2,"text":"02","textPreview":"02","textChars":2,"textLines":1,"bbox":[1180,674,36,20]}
{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/o8lcml","slide":2,"text":"Prediction markets promise transparency, but settlement often introduces interpretation again. A proposer declares an outcome, others may challenge it, and disputed cases can end in a vote. Users can inspect the final transaction, but they still depend on people agreeing about the result."}
