{"kind":"textbox","id":"sh/ixkri94j","slide":4,"text":"Source: TxODDS TxLINE · txodds.net/our-products/tx-line","textPreview":"Source: TxODDS TxLINE · txodds.net/our-products/tx-line","textChars":55,"textLines":1,"bbox":[64,646,800,22]}
{"kind":"textbox","id":"sh/mtsvqh47","slide":4,"text":"04","textPreview":"04","textChars":2,"textLines":1,"bbox":[1180,674,36,20]}
{"kind":"notes","id":"nt/pby4jz","slide":4,"text":"When the match finishes, TxODDS supplies the final score and Merkle proof. The keeper submits that proof to Onside. The Onside program calls the TxODDS oracle program, verifies the value against the on-chain root, and derives the winner from the market predicate. The keeper can submit proof, but it cannot invent a score or select an outcome."}
